The paper deals with wireless communication systems and resource allocation, which are topics commonly found in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas and cloud radio access networks also suggests the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions spatial filtering and beamforming, which are techniques commonly used in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence and Robotics (cs.AR).
